# HALT flag example
#
# When a file named exactly "HALT" (no extension) is placed in this directory
# by the human operator, wake scripts will detect it and stop processing new
# tasks. No new Claude sessions will be launched until the HALT file is removed.
#
# This provides an emergency stop mechanism so the human can pause all
# autonomous agent activity at any time without modifying scripts or configs.
#
# To activate: copy or rename this file to HALT (remove the .example extension).
# To deactivate: delete the HALT file.
